---
/**
 * ai-infrastructure/0001 · Figure 4 — Module 3,
 * "Exact scans everything; ANN searches a fraction".
 * Verbatim from the source HTML. No arrowhead markers used.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Exact k-NN scans every vector and scales linearly; ANN searches only a fraction via a graph or clustering index, trading recall for speed."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Exact scans everything; ANN searches a fraction</text
        >

        <!-- exact -->
        <rect
            x="30"
            y="36"
            width="270"
            height="160"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#10007; Exact k-NN</text
        >
        <text x="165" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >compare query to every vector</text
        >
        <!-- dot field, all checked -->
        <g fill="#9a2417"
            ><circle cx="70" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="100" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="130" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="160" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="190" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="220" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="250" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="70" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="100" cy="125" r="3"></circle><circle cx="130" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="160" cy="125" r="3"></circle><circle cx="190" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="220" cy="125" r="3"></circle><circle cx="250" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle></g
        >
        <text x="165" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >O(n) per query</text
        >
        <text x="165" y="176" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >perfect recall, does not scale</text
        >

        <!-- ann -->
        <rect
            x="340"
            y="36"
            width="270"
            height="160"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; ANN (HNSW / IVF)</text
        >
        <text x="475" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >visit only a few via the index</text
        >
        <g fill="#cbd5cb"
            ><circle cx="380" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="410" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="440" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="500" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="530" cy="100" r="3"></circle><circle cx="560" cy="100" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="380" cy="125" r="3"></circle><circle cx="440" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle><circle cx="500" cy="125" r="3"></circle><circle cx="560" cy="125" r="3"
            ></circle></g
        >
        <g fill="#2f5d3a"
            ><circle cx="470" cy="100" r="4"></circle><circle cx="470" cy="125" r="4"
            ></circle><circle cx="530" cy="125" r="4"></circle></g
        >
        <text x="475" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >~log(n) or cluster-bounded</text
        >
        <text x="475" y="176" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >tiny recall loss, scales to billions</text
        >

        <text x="320" y="218" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >The whole reason a vector DB exists: make billion-vector search interactive by skipping
            most of the corpus.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Exact search is correct but linear — fine for a prototype, fatal at scale. ANN indexes turn
        the scan into a guided traversal, accepting that they may occasionally miss a true neighbor.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3b">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
